July 23, 2026 — system design hardening (branch: fix/system-hardening)

13-issue audit addressed across 8 phases (Phases 1–7 on prior session; Phase 8 + docs this session).

Phase 1 — OTP hashing + attempt cap + SMS fail-fast (auth):
- OTP codes now stored as SHA-256 hashes (codeHash column replaces code); plaintext never persisted
- Verification capped at 5 wrong attempts; 5th attempt locks the OTP (row invisible to next findFirst);
  all failure paths return the same generic 401 to prevent enumeration
- SMS errors surface as HTTP 503 immediately (fail-fast); failed OTP is deleted so quota is not burned;
  users can retry once the outage clears

Phase 2 — Refresh-token reuse detection (auth):
- Added AuthAssertions.isTokenReuse(): true iff revokedAt !== null AND hash matches
- auth.service.refreshToken(): replay of a revoked token family-revokes all active sessions, logs warn, returns generic 401

Phase 3 — Stale-ACCEPTED auto-cancel + expiry notify race fix (bookings):
- Extracted getTimeWindowEndUtcMs() pure function to bookings.constants.ts; assertNoShowWindowOpen uses it
- bookings.cron.expiredPendingBookings(): re-queries confirmed-EXPIRED ids before notifying — prevents notifying
  a booking accepted in the window between findMany and updateMany
- New @Cron(EVERY_HOUR) cancelStaleAcceptedBookings(): auto-cancels ACCEPTED bookings > 24h past their time-window
  end; no strike; skips bookings under active no-show review; notifies both parties fire-and-forget

Phase 4 — Push tickets + receipt cron + token pruning (notifications):
- New PushTicket model (push_tickets table) — persists ok tickets for receipt polling
- notifications.service: ok ticket ids persisted; DeviceNotRegistered error → immediate token prune
- New notifications.cron (PUSH_RECEIPT_CRON every 15 min): polls Expo receipts, prunes dead tokens,
  deletes resolved tickets, ages out tickets > 24h

Phase 5 — rankingScore denormalized column (workers/reviews):
- Added rankingScore Decimal(3,2) to worker_profiles; backfilled from averageRating for workers with ≥3 reviews
- New rating.util.ts: computeWorkerRatingUpdate() returns {averageRating, totalReviews, rankingScore}
- reviews.service and admin.service now call the util on every review create/delete
- workers.service search orderBy: [rankingScore desc, totalReviews desc, createdAt desc]; masked workers sort last

Phase 6 — DB-record-based file authorization (uploads):
- UploadsAssertions.assertCanReadProtectedFile() rewritten: looks up owning DB record by storedUrl instead of
  relying on path layout; no record → 404 for everyone including admin (orphan files unreachable)
- Orphan-file sweep deferred (disk-space only risk now, not data exposure; asymmetric failure risk from a sweep bug)

Phase 7 — Auth retention cron (auth):
- New auth.constants.ts: REFRESH_TOKEN_RETENTION_MS = 30d; OTP_RETENTION_MS = 24h added to otp.constants.ts
- New AuthCron: @Cron(EVERY_DAY_AT_6PM) — 18:00 UTC = 02:00 Asia/Manila off-peak; purges OTPs >24h,
  revoked/expired refresh tokens >30d; each purge in independent try/catch

Phase 8 — Ops: health endpoint, graceful shutdown, per-user throttling, CORS via config:
- GET /health (@Public): calls prisma.$queryRaw SELECT 1; returns {status:'ok',db:'up'} or 503
- PrismaService.onModuleDestroy(): $disconnect() on graceful shutdown
- main.ts: app.enableShutdownHooks(); CORS_ORIGIN read from typed appConfig (not raw process.env);
  Swagger NODE_ENV check also uses appConfig
- New AppThrottlerGuard: extends ThrottlerGuard, getTracker → req.user?.sub ?? req.ip ?? ''
  (per-user throttling for authenticated routes; public routes fall back to IP)
- Swapped ThrottlerGuard → AppThrottlerGuard in APP_GUARD providers
- appConfig Zod schema: added CORS_ORIGIN optional field

Docs:
- BRD v1.4 → v1.5: AUTH-05 hashed codes note; new AUTH-10 (attempt cap, generic errors);
  AUTH-11 (reuse family revocation); BKG-11 (system auto-cancel, no strike, both-party push);
  BKG-11 reference in CANCELLED status; REV-04 rankingScore explanation; worker_profiles schema row
  updated; Notifications NFR (receipt polling, token pruning); File Access Control NFR updated;
  new Data Retention NFR (OTP 24h, refresh 30d); §9.8 Operations Endpoints (GET /health);
  risk register: SMS fail-fast, orphan files deferred, push delivery improved
- Handout: request-otp 503 behavior; verify-otp lockout (5 wrong = re-request, same 401);
  refresh reuse detection (family revoke → force re-login); CANCELLED enum entry updated;
  new §16 Health / Ops Endpoints; ToC updated

Test count: 303 → 341 (38 new tests across auth, bookings, notifications, uploads, workers, app specs)

